WEBVTT

00:12.012 --> 00:13.679
MY FIRST PROM TUX, HUH?

00:13.847 --> 00:17.349
COME ON, GUYS.
DIG THE CRUSHED VELVET.

00:17.517 --> 00:21.145
ERIC, YOU LOOK
LIKE A PIMP.

00:21.312 --> 00:23.439
YOU KNOW, FORMAN,
PROM NIGHT COULD BE

00:23.606 --> 00:26.191
A VERY SPECIAL NIGHT
FOR YOU AND DONNA.

00:26.359 --> 00:28.610
THIS COULD BE THE BIGGEST
NIGHT OF OUR LIVES.

00:28.778 --> 00:30.362
I MEAN, DONNA
AND I COULD GO...

00:30.530 --> 00:33.323
TO THE PROM.

00:33.491 --> 00:34.908
NO, FEZ, ALL THE WAY.

00:35.076 --> 00:36.535
ALL THE WAY...

00:36.703 --> 00:39.872
TO THE PROM.

00:40.040 --> 00:41.040
KNOW WHAT YOU SHOULD DO?

00:41.207 --> 00:42.458
YOU SHOULD DEFINITELY
RENT A MOTEL ROOM.

00:42.625 --> 00:45.169
OH, YEAH,
THAT'S SPONTANEOUS.

00:45.336 --> 00:46.837
WHAT?

00:47.005 --> 00:49.048
LOOK, IF THIS NIGHT
IS AS BIG AS I THINK,

00:49.215 --> 00:51.550
I WANT IT TO BE
VERY, VERY SPECIAL,

00:51.718 --> 00:52.968
BECAUSE THIS IS GONNA BE
THE FIRST TIME

00:53.136 --> 00:54.720
FOR BOTH OF US.

00:54.888 --> 00:57.514
OH, YOU SILLY VIRGINS.

00:58.558 --> 01:01.518
ANYWAY, THIS IS
HOW I PICTURED IT.

01:03.396 --> 01:09.151
WELL, HERE WE ARE...
WALKING ON THE BEACH...

01:09.319 --> 01:12.488
AND NOW
WE'RE GONNA DO IT.

01:12.655 --> 01:14.865
YES, YES.

01:15.033 --> 01:16.533
ISN'T IT SPONTANEOUS?

01:16.701 --> 01:20.621
EXACTLY.
THAT'S WHAT GOT ME.

01:25.710 --> 01:27.836
AH, THAT WAS NICE.

01:29.255 --> 01:33.926
BUT IF I PLAN IT OUT,
IT WON'T BE NICE, IT'LL BE...

01:34.094 --> 01:35.094
GOOD EVENING.

01:35.261 --> 01:36.178
DID YOU BRING THE FORMS?

01:36.346 --> 01:37.346
YES, I DID.

01:37.514 --> 01:38.722
HERE'S THE GUARANTEE
OF FOREPLAY,

01:38.890 --> 01:41.475
SIGNED, INITIALED,
NOTARIZED.

01:41.643 --> 01:43.310
VERY WELL.

01:43.478 --> 01:44.561
AS YOU KNOW,
I'M ON THE PILL,

01:44.729 --> 01:47.564
SO HERE IS YOUR COPY OF
THE PROPHYLACTIC WAIVER.

01:47.732 --> 01:49.149
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE WE HAVE
A DEAL HERE.

01:49.317 --> 01:50.359
I'M LOOKING FORWARD
TO CONSUMMATION.

01:50.527 --> 01:52.694
EXCELLENT.
THANK YOU.

01:52.862 --> 01:54.446
FORMAN, IF YOU
DON'T GET A MOTEL,

01:54.614 --> 01:56.615
IT'S GONNA BE
MORE LIKE THIS.

02:00.411 --> 02:03.122
YOU'RE HOME ALREADY?
IT'S NOT EVEN 10:00.

02:03.289 --> 02:04.957
YOU DIDN'T HAVE A PLAN,
DID YOU?

02:05.125 --> 02:07.126
KITTY, HE'S HOME ALREADY.

02:07.293 --> 02:08.377
ALREADY?

02:08.545 --> 02:11.839
OH, ERIC, YOU'RE JUST
SUCH A LOSER.

02:14.300 --> 02:15.592
HE IS, ISN'T HE?

02:15.760 --> 02:20.597
[LAUGHING]

02:29.649 --> 02:32.943
♪ HANGIN' OUT ♪

02:33.111 --> 02:36.655
♪ DOWN THE STREET ♪

02:36.823 --> 02:40.284
♪ THE SAME OLD THING ♪

02:40.451 --> 02:43.787
♪ WE DID LAST WEEK ♪

02:43.955 --> 02:47.749
♪ NOT A THING TO DO ♪

02:47.917 --> 02:50.961
♪ BUT TALK TO YOU ♪

02:51.129 --> 02:53.380
♪ OH, YEAH ♪

02:53.548 --> 02:56.425
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE BY
CARSEY-WERNER
AND FOX BROADCASTING

02:56.593 --> 02:58.802
HELLO, WISCONSIN!

03:01.514 --> 03:04.308
ARE YOU READY
TO ROCK AND ROLL?

03:05.602 --> 03:07.644
KITTY, I AM SO MAD
AT BOB.

03:07.812 --> 03:10.105
I'M TRYING TO IMPROVE MYSELF,
AND HE WON'T LET ME.

03:10.273 --> 03:12.816
PLUS, HE SAYS MY IDEAS
ARE STUPID.

03:12.984 --> 03:14.193
OH WELL, NOW,
THAT'S THE POT

03:14.360 --> 03:16.904
CALLING THE KETTLE
BLACK, ISN'T IT?

03:17.071 --> 03:20.949
I'LL SAY, WHAT?
WHAT?

03:26.206 --> 03:28.165
GOOD COFFEE.

03:30.001 --> 03:31.084
YOU KNOW,
I'M SORRY, MIDGE,

03:31.252 --> 03:33.670
BUT I REALLY
HAVE TO GET TO WORK.

03:33.838 --> 03:36.089
GOSH DARN IT,
I WANT A JOB!

03:36.257 --> 03:37.716
YOU KNOW, MIDGE,

03:37.884 --> 03:39.676
HAVING A JOB IS NOT ALL
IT'S CRACKED UP TO BE.

03:39.844 --> 03:42.054
WORKING AT THE HOSPITAL
IS VERY HARD WORK.

03:42.222 --> 03:43.722
BUT I DON'T WANT
ONE OF THOSE JOBS.

03:43.890 --> 03:46.850
I WANT A FUN JOB.

03:47.018 --> 03:50.729
OKAY, WELL,
EVEN WITH A FUN JOB,

03:50.897 --> 03:53.148
YOU STILL HAVE TO DEAL
WITH YOUR BOSS.

03:53.316 --> 03:57.027
YEAH, RIGHT.
I'LL GET A JOB AS A BOSS.

03:58.238 --> 04:02.824
WELL, NOW, THAT IS
A SHARP PLAN, MIDGE.

04:03.576 --> 04:07.287
YOU JUST LET ME KNOW
HOW THAT GOES.

04:09.040 --> 04:14.002
OKAY, GUYS, GUESS WHO'S TAKING
PAM MACY TO THE PROM?

04:14.170 --> 04:17.297
ANYONE WITH A QUARTER?

04:18.633 --> 04:20.842
ME!

04:21.010 --> 04:23.929
DAMN, AND I HAD A QUARTER!

04:26.057 --> 04:27.557
HEY, KELSO, YOU'RE
NOT TAKING JACKIE?

04:27.725 --> 04:31.144
NO WAY, MAN.
JACKIE DUMPED ME.

04:31.896 --> 04:33.897
HEY, I CAN TAKE JACKIE.

04:34.065 --> 04:36.817
DO IT, FEZ, AND
I'LL KICK YOUR ASS.

04:37.568 --> 04:39.611
WELL, WELL, WELL.

04:39.779 --> 04:42.030
LOOK WHO SUDDENLY CARES.

04:42.782 --> 04:44.241
OW.
WHY DID YOU HIT ME?

04:44.409 --> 04:46.910
THAT WAS SARCASM.

04:51.916 --> 04:54.501
YOU GUYS ARE MAKING ME SICK
WITH ALL YOUR PROM TALK.

04:54.669 --> 04:56.586
PROMS ARE STUPID.

04:56.754 --> 04:57.754
HYDE, WHAT
WOULD YOU KNOW?

04:57.922 --> 04:59.047
YOU'VE NEVER
EVEN BEEN TO ONE.

04:59.215 --> 05:00.590
WELL, I HAVEN'T BEEN
TO THE DENTIST EITHER,

05:00.758 --> 05:03.635
BUT I DON'T NEED TO GO
TO KNOW IT'S LAME.

05:05.555 --> 05:08.598
OH, I KNOW WHO I CAN
ASK TO THE PROM.

05:08.766 --> 05:12.102
OH BOY!
WHO, FEZ?

05:12.270 --> 05:17.149
THE LUCKY LADY IS...
MY ENGLISH TEACHER.

05:19.485 --> 05:23.530
FEZ, YOU CAN'T TAKE
A TEACHER TO THE PROM.

05:23.698 --> 05:24.698
WHY NOT?

05:24.866 --> 05:30.120
SHE'S ALWAYS WRITING SEXY
COMMENTS ON MY HOMEWORK.

05:30.288 --> 05:35.834
"NICE JOB."
"GOOD EFFORT."

05:36.002 --> 05:41.965
"SEE ME."
"I LOVE YOU."

05:43.926 --> 05:46.803
OKAY, I MADE
THE LAST ONE UP.

05:46.971 --> 05:49.723
BUT THE OTHER ONES
WERE REAL.

05:51.851 --> 05:53.518
THESE ARE THE SHOES
I'M WEARING TO THE PROM.

05:53.686 --> 05:54.811
AREN'T THEY COOL?

05:54.979 --> 05:58.065
OH MY GOD, I WAS
GONNA GET NEW SHOES...

05:58.232 --> 06:00.984
EXCEPT MICHAEL
DIDN'T ASK ME.

06:01.152 --> 06:03.278
YOU LIKE
MY PROM DRESS, RIGHT?

06:04.405 --> 06:05.489
OH MY GOD.

06:05.656 --> 06:08.325
I WAS GONNA GET
A NEW PROM DRESS...

06:08.493 --> 06:11.536
EXCEPT MICHAEL
DIDN'T ASK ME.

06:11.704 --> 06:13.872
I'M SO NERVOUS
ABOUT THE PROM.

06:14.665 --> 06:17.167
I THINK IT'S GONNA BE
THE NIGHT THAT ERIC AND I...

06:17.335 --> 06:19.169
YOU KNOW.

06:19.337 --> 06:20.837
OH MY GOSH, THAT'S
WHEN MICHAEL AND I

06:21.005 --> 06:22.964
WERE GONNA DO IT
FOR THE FIRST TIME.

06:23.132 --> 06:26.093
JACKIE, YOU AND KELSO
DID IT, LIKE, 2 MONTHS AGO

06:26.260 --> 06:29.763
AND LIKE, 30 TIMES
AFTER THAT.

06:29.931 --> 06:33.350
YEAH, BUT IT WOULD HAVE BEEN
OUR FIRST TIME AT A PROM.

06:35.937 --> 06:39.189
EXCEPT MICHAEL
DIDN'T ASK ME.

06:39.357 --> 06:42.317
JACKIE, YOU BROKE UP
WITH HIM.

06:42.485 --> 06:45.695
I KNOW.
ISN'T IT SAD?

06:47.365 --> 06:49.616
LOOK, JUST ASK KELSO
TO GO WITH YOU.

06:49.784 --> 06:51.785
GOD, NO.
THIS IS THE PROM.

06:51.953 --> 06:55.580
THIS IS NO TIME FOR YOUR
STUPID FEMINIST CRAP.

07:00.211 --> 07:02.629
HELLO, MICHAEL.

07:02.797 --> 07:05.841
HELLO, JACKIE.

07:06.008 --> 07:07.843
I'M JUST OVER HERE
HELPING DONNA GET READY

07:08.010 --> 07:10.846
FOR THE PROM, BECAUSE
ERIC AND DONNA

07:11.013 --> 07:12.889
ARE GOING TO THE PROM.

07:13.057 --> 07:15.350
YES, WE ARE.

07:16.978 --> 07:19.354
I'M GOING TO THE PROM.

07:19.522 --> 07:21.898
I'M TAKING PAM MACY.

07:22.733 --> 07:25.360
OH, THE THING.

07:27.238 --> 07:28.989
OH.

07:29.157 --> 07:31.283
WELL, I HAVE
A DATE TOO.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.827
WHO IS IT?
WHAT'S HIS NAME?

07:33.995 --> 07:36.663
HIS NAME IS...
NOT IMPORTANT.

07:36.831 --> 07:39.958
WHAT'S IMPORTANT IS
HE'S BETTER THAN YOU

07:40.126 --> 07:43.211
IN EVERY CONCEIVABLE WAY.

07:47.091 --> 07:50.051
DAMN, JACKIE,
THAT COULD BE ANYBODY!

08:00.771 --> 08:02.898
[SIGHS]

08:04.609 --> 08:07.402
HMM.

08:08.279 --> 08:10.947
JACKIE, IF I ASKED YOU
WHAT'S WRONG,

08:11.115 --> 08:14.117
WILL YOU STOP DOING THAT?

08:14.285 --> 08:15.827
IT'S THE PROM.

08:15.995 --> 08:18.246
STUPID MICHAEL'S
TAKING STUPID PAM MACY,

08:18.414 --> 08:20.415
AND I DON'T HAVE A DATE,
BUT I TOLD HIM I DID.

08:20.583 --> 08:22.501
I'M A COMPLETE LOSER.

08:22.668 --> 08:25.754
[LAUGHING]

08:30.801 --> 08:34.471
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

08:34.639 --> 08:38.475
IT'S JUST THAT, I THOUGHT
HE WAS GONNA ASK ME,

08:38.643 --> 08:41.311
AND NOW EVERYONE WHO'S
ANYONE IS ALREADY GOING.

08:41.479 --> 08:43.522
OH, THAT IS SO TRUE.

08:43.689 --> 08:46.691
HOW ABOUT YOU?
YOU'RE NOT EVEN GOING.

08:46.859 --> 08:49.152
[GASPS]
YOU'RE NOT EVEN GOING!

08:49.320 --> 08:51.530
OH, AND I BET
YOU CLEAN UP REAL GOOD.

08:53.824 --> 08:57.202
WELL, I DO,
BUT I WON'T.

08:57.370 --> 09:00.247
SEE, THAT'S
A BIG PART OF WHO I AM.

09:00.998 --> 09:02.582
LOOK, I KNOW WE'VE HAD
OUR DIFFERENCES, BUT...

09:02.750 --> 09:05.460
JACKIE, WE'VE HAD
NOTHING BUT DIFFERENCES.

09:05.628 --> 09:09.256
IN FACT, DON'T WE KIND
OF HATE EACH OTHER?

09:09.423 --> 09:12.092
YES, BUT THIS IS THE PROM!

09:12.260 --> 09:15.762
[SOBBING]

09:15.930 --> 09:19.516
JACKIE, DON'T.
STOP.

09:19.684 --> 09:22.644
STOP CRYING.
STOP IT.

09:23.437 --> 09:25.021
LOOK, DO YOU WANNA GO
TO THE PROM?

09:25.189 --> 09:27.148
YES.

09:33.948 --> 09:37.200
♪♪♪

09:37.368 --> 09:40.704
♪ SLOW RIDE ♪

09:40.871 --> 09:44.624
♪ TAKE IT EASY ♪

09:45.751 --> 09:47.794
THE GYM LOOKS LIKE...

09:47.962 --> 09:49.796
WELL, THE GYM
WITH STREAMERS,

09:49.964 --> 09:51.381
BUT IT'S NICE.

09:51.549 --> 09:52.507
YEAH.

09:52.675 --> 09:55.218
THIS IS GONNA BE
AN INCREDIBLE NIGHT.

09:55.386 --> 09:57.554
REALLY INCREDIBLE.

09:57.722 --> 10:00.724
WAIT.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

10:00.891 --> 10:02.434
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

10:02.602 --> 10:03.977
NOTHING.

10:04.145 --> 10:07.022
OKAY, THEN ME NEITHER.

10:07.231 --> 10:08.398
HEY, GUYS.

10:08.566 --> 10:10.609
PAM, THIS IS
ERIC AND DONNA.

10:10.776 --> 10:13.236
WE HAVE OUR BIOLOGY
CLASS TOGETHER.

10:13.404 --> 10:16.448
BIOLOGY?

10:16.616 --> 10:18.533
YEAH.

10:18.701 --> 10:23.413
SEE, PAM DOESN'T LIKE
TO TALK ABOUT SCHOOL.

10:23.581 --> 10:25.373
ARE YOU GUYS
HAVING FUN?

10:25.541 --> 10:27.500
NO.

10:27.668 --> 10:30.128
I HAVE TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

10:31.422 --> 10:33.590
MY GOD, KELSO, YOU BROUGHT
HER INSTEAD OF JACKIE.

10:33.758 --> 10:34.674
HEY, I LOVE HER.

10:34.842 --> 10:36.301
NO, YOU DON'T.

10:36.469 --> 10:38.428
OKAY, I DON'T.

10:38.596 --> 10:41.056
SEE, BUT JACKIE'S
GONNA BE REALLY JEALOUS.

10:41.223 --> 10:44.601
GOOD EVENING, KIDS.
SO, IS EVERYONE HAVING FUN?

10:44.769 --> 10:47.854
WHY, YES, WE ARE,
MISS KAVINSKY.

10:49.774 --> 10:50.982
THERE YOU ARE,
DIANE.

10:51.150 --> 10:54.527
I'VE BEEN LOOKING
ALL OVER FOR YOU.

10:54.695 --> 10:56.279
SHALL WE DANCE?

10:56.447 --> 10:58.948
I'M NOT GOING TO DANCE
WITH YOU, FEZ.

11:01.077 --> 11:04.037
ISN'T SHE ADORABLE?

11:11.462 --> 11:15.382
(EDNA)
THEY'RE ALL
GONNA LAUGH AT YOU!

11:15.549 --> 11:16.466
SHUT UP, MA!

11:16.634 --> 11:19.260
YOU'RE MAKING THE NIGHT
TOO DAMN SPECIAL!

11:22.306 --> 11:24.265
HEY.

11:27.019 --> 11:29.145
WOW, YOU LOOK
BEAUTIFUL.

11:29.313 --> 11:31.815
OH MY GOD.
SO DO YOU.

11:32.650 --> 11:36.027
UM, DO YOU WANT ME TO GO
INSIDE AND MEET YOUR...

11:36.195 --> 11:38.238
NO, NO, TRUST ME,
SHE'S LOVELY.

11:39.699 --> 11:41.741
LET'S JUST GO,
ALL RIGHT?

11:42.618 --> 11:44.411
IS THAT FOR ME?

11:44.578 --> 11:47.247
OH YEAH, HERE.
I GOT THIS FOR YOU.

11:48.582 --> 11:52.502
OH GOD, STEVE,
THIS IS BEAUTIFUL.

11:52.670 --> 11:53.962
YOU KNOW, THIS WHOLE
EXPERIENCE HAS TAUGHT ME

11:54.130 --> 11:56.548
THAT YOU DON'T NEED MICHAEL
TO GO TO THE PROM.

11:56.716 --> 11:58.883
I CAN GO WITH ANYONE...

11:59.051 --> 12:02.429
EVEN YOU.

12:02.596 --> 12:04.931
THANKS.

12:08.310 --> 12:10.645
OKAY, LET'S
NOT DO THAT.

12:11.731 --> 12:14.691
SORRY, UM, I HAVE
MY DAD'S LINCOLN.

12:14.859 --> 12:16.151
WILL YOU DRIVE?

12:16.318 --> 12:18.862
YEAH, HE'S GOT
INSURANCE, RIGHT?

12:20.364 --> 12:23.158
WAIT, I DON'T CARE.
LET'S GO.

12:24.869 --> 12:26.119
I'VE DECIDED WHAT
KIND OF BUSINESS

12:26.287 --> 12:27.871
I'M GONNA OPEN.

12:28.038 --> 12:32.208
WHAT'S THE ONE THING PEOPLE
CAN'T LIVE WITHOUT?

12:32.376 --> 12:36.629
OXYGEN.

12:36.797 --> 12:38.381
NO.

12:38.549 --> 12:41.634
NO, NO, NO,
THAT'S TRUE.

12:41.802 --> 12:43.386
BUT IT'S NOT
WHAT I'M SELLING,

12:43.554 --> 12:45.722
SO KEEP GUESSING.

12:45.890 --> 12:47.432
LEMONADE?

12:47.600 --> 12:49.684
UH-UH.
GIVE UP?

12:49.852 --> 12:51.394
I'M ABOUT TO.

12:51.562 --> 12:53.730
GREETING CARDS.

12:53.898 --> 12:57.192
[LAUGHING]

13:00.946 --> 13:03.823
GOOD WINE.

13:04.742 --> 13:10.121
♪ I'M NOT ALONE... ♪

13:10.289 --> 13:12.749
THIS IS SUCH
A GREAT NIGHT.

13:12.917 --> 13:15.418
YEAH.

13:15.586 --> 13:18.171
IT'S TOO BAD OUR PARENTS
AREN'T OUT OF TOWN

13:18.339 --> 13:23.927
SO WE'D HAVE
SOMEPLACE TO GO...

13:24.094 --> 13:26.596
FOR AFTER.

13:26.764 --> 13:31.351
YEAH, LIKE...
A MOTEL ROOM.

13:32.603 --> 13:36.105
YEAH, THAT WOULD
HAVE BEEN GREAT.

13:36.273 --> 13:39.692
REALLY?
'CAUSE I GOT ONE.

13:39.860 --> 13:43.446
DID YOU PLAN ON
TELLING ME?

13:43.614 --> 13:47.450
NO.

13:47.618 --> 13:50.203
WELL, IT'S BETTER
THAT YOU DIDN'T

13:50.371 --> 13:52.664
'CAUSE THEN IT WOULDN'T
HAVE BEEN SPONTANEOUS.

13:52.832 --> 13:57.126
SPONT... OH, YOU ARE
SO THE GIRL FOR ME.

13:57.962 --> 14:00.380
LET'S GO.

14:01.131 --> 14:03.424
OKAY.

14:08.430 --> 14:10.223
WHY SO GLUM, FEZ?

14:10.391 --> 14:14.310
WELL, MRS. CLARK, YOU MAY BE
GOOD AT TEACHING THE MUSIC,

14:14.478 --> 14:17.897
BUT YOU CANNOT HELP ME
IN THE WAYS OF LOVE.

14:18.065 --> 14:20.483
FEZ, HAS SOMEONE
GOT YOU DOWN?

14:20.651 --> 14:23.570
SO FAR DOWN, MRS. CLARK.

14:23.737 --> 14:25.321
HERE'S A LITTLE DITTY
I'VE BEEN WORKING ON.

14:25.489 --> 14:27.949
MAYBE IT'LL HELP.
HIT IT.

14:29.451 --> 14:34.163
[PIANO PLAYING]

14:34.331 --> 14:37.458
♪ FIRST I WAS AFRAID,
I WAS PETRIFIED ♪

14:37.626 --> 14:39.669
♪ I KEPT THINKING
I COULD NEVER LIVE ♪

14:39.837 --> 14:41.671
♪ WITHOUT YOU BY MY SIDE ♪

14:41.839 --> 14:43.840
♪ BUT THEN I SPENT
SO MANY NIGHTS ♪

14:44.008 --> 14:45.675
♪ THINKING HOW
YOU DID ME WRONG ♪

14:45.843 --> 14:47.802
♪ AND I GREW STRONG ♪

14:47.970 --> 14:49.679
♪ AND I LEARNED
HOW TO GET ALONG ♪

14:49.847 --> 14:51.806
♪ SO NOW YOU'RE BACK ♪

14:51.974 --> 14:53.850
♪ FROM OUTER SPACE ♪

14:54.018 --> 14:55.643
♪ I JUST WALKED IN
TO FIND YOU HERE ♪

14:55.811 --> 14:57.854
♪ WITH THAT SAD LOOK
UPON YOUR FACE ♪

14:58.022 --> 14:59.939
♪ I SHOULDA CHANGED
THAT STUPID LOCK ♪

15:00.107 --> 15:02.317
♪ I SHOULDA MADE
YOU LEAVE YOUR KEY ♪

15:02.484 --> 15:04.277
♪ IF I'D A KNOWN
FOR JUST ONE SECOND ♪

15:04.445 --> 15:06.029
♪ YOU'D BE BACK
TO BOTHER ME ♪

15:06.196 --> 15:08.239
♪ GO ON, NOW, GO ♪

15:08.407 --> 15:10.199
♪ WALK OUT THE DOOR ♪

15:10.367 --> 15:12.327
♪ JUST TURN AROUND NOW ♪

15:12.494 --> 15:15.330
♪ 'CAUSE YOU'RE NOT
WELCOME ANYMORE ♪

15:15.497 --> 15:17.415
♪ WEREN'T YOU THE ONE
WHO TRIED TO HURT ME ♪

15:17.583 --> 15:18.833
♪ WITH GOOD-BYE? ♪

15:19.001 --> 15:20.668
♪ YOU THINK I'D CRUMBLE? ♪

15:20.836 --> 15:22.462
♪ YOU THINK I'D LAY DOWN
AND DIE? ♪

15:22.630 --> 15:24.839
♪ OH NO, NOT I ♪

15:25.007 --> 15:27.717
♪ I WILL SURVIVE ♪

15:29.219 --> 15:34.182
♪♪♪

15:38.479 --> 15:40.021
MIDGE, YOU DON'T KNOW
THE FIRST THING

15:40.189 --> 15:41.481
ABOUT HAVING A BUSINESS.

15:41.649 --> 15:43.232
BUT THERE'S NO RISK, BOB.

15:43.400 --> 15:44.567
WHY NOT?

15:44.735 --> 15:47.737
BECAUSE IT'S YOUR MONEY.

15:51.408 --> 15:53.952
KITTY, DON'T YOU THINK
I SHOULD HAVE

15:54.119 --> 15:56.079
MY OWN CARD SHOP?

15:56.246 --> 15:57.997
MIDGIE, HOLD ON.

15:58.165 --> 16:00.166
I THINK I HAVE
A DYNAMITE SOLUTION.

16:00.334 --> 16:01.584
REALLY?

16:01.752 --> 16:03.670
OH YEAH...

16:03.837 --> 16:06.172
'CAUSE I LOVE YOU.

16:06.340 --> 16:07.924
SO I WANT YOU TO HAVE
ANOTHER BABY

16:08.092 --> 16:10.468
AND STOP BUGGING ME.

16:10.636 --> 16:13.054
OH BOB, NO.

16:22.231 --> 16:24.899
SO HOW MUCH THIS WHOLE SETUP
GONNA COST YOU, BOB?

16:25.067 --> 16:26.067
PLENTY.

16:26.235 --> 16:29.195
BUT I FIGURE IT'LL BE
CHEAPER THAN A DIVORCE.

16:32.282 --> 16:34.242
WE'LL SEE.

16:39.456 --> 16:42.291
AND NOW HERE WE ARE.

16:42.459 --> 16:44.836
THIS IS SO ROMANTIC.

16:47.840 --> 16:50.925
HEY, IT'S FORMAN AND DONNA,
AND THEY'RE GONNA DO IT!

16:51.719 --> 16:54.887
[CHANTING]
FORMAN, FORMAN, FORMAN!

16:55.055 --> 17:01.811
FORMAN, FORMAN, FORMAN!
FORMAN, FORMAN, FORMAN!

17:01.979 --> 17:05.273
[CHEERING]

17:09.319 --> 17:11.320
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THOSE GUYS ARE JUST JERKS.

17:11.488 --> 17:13.948
HEY, I FORGOT
ABOUT 'EM ALREADY.

17:20.414 --> 17:22.832
HANG ON, HANG ON.
BIG STAIN, BIG STAIN.

17:27.838 --> 17:29.297
I'M JUST GONNA
GO GRAB A TOWEL.

17:29.465 --> 17:31.507
OKAY.

17:34.678 --> 17:37.138
OH, GOOD GOD!

17:40.976 --> 17:42.351
YOU KNOW, THEY SAY THEY'RE
MORE SCARED OF YOU

17:42.519 --> 17:45.146
THAN YOU ARE OF THEM, MICE.

17:58.535 --> 17:59.535
YOU KNOW, DONNA,

17:59.703 --> 18:03.206
I'VE THOUGHT ABOUT THIS MOMENT,
LIKE, A THOUSAND TIMES.

18:03.457 --> 18:06.125
ME TOO.

18:09.546 --> 18:12.048
(MALE OUTSIDE)
ONE, TWO, THREE!

18:12.216 --> 18:14.509
[CRASHING]

18:14.676 --> 18:18.596
[KIDS CHEERING]

18:24.645 --> 18:26.062
HEY, WHEN YOU THOUGHT
ABOUT THIS MOMENT,

18:26.230 --> 18:29.148
WAS IT LIKE THIS?

18:29.316 --> 18:31.275
NOT REALLY.

18:33.695 --> 18:35.071
YOU KNOW, I WAS HAVING
A PRETTY GOOD TIME

18:35.239 --> 18:38.324
AT THE PROM.

18:38.492 --> 18:41.035
ME TOO.

18:43.705 --> 18:45.248
LET'S GET OUTTA HERE.

18:45.415 --> 18:46.666
OKAY.

18:46.834 --> 18:52.088
UM, DONNA, WHAT IF THIS
IS OUR ONLY CHANCE?

18:54.550 --> 18:56.926
IT WON'T BE.

18:57.928 --> 18:59.887
OKAY.

19:07.813 --> 19:09.605
IT'S JUST THAT
I ALWAYS PICTURED

19:09.773 --> 19:11.774
MICHAEL AND I
TOGETHER AT THE PROM.

19:11.942 --> 19:13.317
THAT'S THE WAY IT
WAS SUPPOSED TO BE,

19:13.485 --> 19:15.111
YOU KNOW?

19:15.279 --> 19:17.947
YEAH, I KNOW.

19:18.115 --> 19:21.409
WELL, HEY, PAM'S BUTT
LOOKS REALLY BIG

19:21.577 --> 19:23.995
IN THAT DRESS.

19:24.163 --> 19:26.122
NO, IT DOESN'T.

19:26.290 --> 19:30.168
YEAH.
NO, IT DOESN'T.

19:30.335 --> 19:32.461
BUT THANK YOU.

19:32.629 --> 19:35.339
UM, DO YOU MIND
IF WE JUST SIT DOWN?

19:35.507 --> 19:38.092
YEAH, OKAY, I'LL GO
GRAB SOME PUNCH.

19:42.890 --> 19:46.851
HYDE, YOU BROUGHT
JACKIE TO THE PROM?

19:47.019 --> 19:48.477
YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE MY FRIEND,

19:48.645 --> 19:50.104
AND YOU DOGGED ME!

19:50.272 --> 19:53.691
HEY, SHE CRIED, MAN.

19:55.068 --> 19:58.029
WELL, IS SHE
HAVING A GOOD TIME?

20:00.866 --> 20:03.784
'CAUSE SHE LOOKS
REAL PRETTY.

20:03.952 --> 20:05.703
ALL RIGHT,
LOOK, YOU BIG BABY.

20:05.871 --> 20:08.372
SHE WANTS TO BE WITH YOU,
AND YOU WANNA BE WITH HER.

20:08.540 --> 20:09.957
SO WHY DON'T YOU STOP
WHINING ABOUT IT

20:10.125 --> 20:11.667
AND JUST GO BE
WITH EACH OTHER?

20:11.835 --> 20:14.545
'CAUSE THE WHOLE THING
SICKENS ME.

20:15.672 --> 20:18.049
BUT WHAT AM I
GONNA DO WITH PAM?

20:18.800 --> 20:21.177
[SIGHS]

20:21.345 --> 20:23.763
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF PAM.

20:32.231 --> 20:34.273
EXCUSE ME, PAM?

20:34.942 --> 20:38.319
HI, HAVE YOU EVER
SEEN THE BACK SEAT

20:38.487 --> 20:40.863
OF A LINCOLN CONTINENTAL?

20:41.031 --> 20:43.658
LOTS OF TIMES.

20:43.825 --> 20:45.743
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO SEE ANOTHER ONE?

20:45.911 --> 20:47.745
SURE.

20:47.913 --> 20:49.872
THAT'S GREAT,
THAT'S GREAT.

21:00.425 --> 21:01.634
JACKIE?

21:01.802 --> 21:03.094
MICHAEL?

21:03.262 --> 21:04.720
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

21:04.888 --> 21:07.515
YOU LOOK REALLY HANDSOME.

21:07.683 --> 21:09.267
I MISS YOU.

21:09.434 --> 21:11.727
I MISS YOU TOO.

21:15.274 --> 21:22.738
♪ LORD KNOWS,
I CAN'T CHANGE ♪

21:22.906 --> 21:27.076
♪ NO, LORD,
I CAN'T CHANGE ♪

21:27.244 --> 21:30.538
♪ WON'T YOU FLY? ♪

21:30.706 --> 21:34.000
♪ FREE BIRD ♪

21:35.085 --> 21:40.047
